Why only one action
There's a subtle design decision here worth surfacing: when we're in Case Unmapped, the BP might already have a non-null pei_owningbu from a previous cycle (when admin had resolved the mapping, BP got the BU written, then admin later un-resolved the mapping by clearing Target BU). The current Parent BP value should NOT be cleared just because the mapping is now blank — that would silently break BPs whose admin un-mapped them temporarily.
So Case Unmapped deliberately leaves Parent BP's pei_owningbu alone. ADR-024 (engagement scope immutability) backs this — once a BU is assigned to a BP in an active cycle, the only way to clear it is admin action, not auto-revert from blank mapping.
If you'd ever want to change this behavior (e.g., add a "clear BP Owning BU when mapping is unmapped" step), that's a separate decision and a separate ADR. For L1-A08 we keep it conservative.
